        <item>
            <title>2.0.0</title>
            <pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 19:25:12 +0900</pubDate>
            <link>https://github.com/Saqoosha/Canopy</link>
            <sparkle:version>38</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>2.0.0</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>15.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <sparkle:hardwareRequirements>arm64</sparkle:hardwareRequirements>
            <description sparkle:format="markdown"><![CDATA[Canopy 2.0 reorganizes the entire shell around a single window with a persistent sidebar, brings Claude Code on the Web sessions into the native app, and polishes Settings to match macOS conventions.

### Features

- **Single-window sidebar shell** — Sessions now live in a persistent left-hand sidebar, Arc/Chrome-style. Switching between sessions swaps the active WKWebView in place, so live state is preserved and switching is near-instant. The Launcher row sits at the top of the sidebar with directory picker, model/effort/permission selectors, and recent-session history.
- **Claude Code on the Web teleport** — Cloud sessions you started at claude.ai/code now show up directly in the sidebar. Click one to teleport it into Canopy and continue locally with full streaming.
- **Sidebar status icons at a glance** — Each row shows live status: spinner while spawning, yellow hand when waiting for a permission decision, animated flower while thinking, dot when idle, and a cloud or computer icon for closed sessions.
- **Sidebar filter & hide** — A gear popover lets you filter the sidebar by status, origin, project, or recency, and right-click → "Hide from sidebar" suppresses individual rows.
- **Default permission mode for Recents** — The new Settings → Permissions tab adds a Default for Recents picker, so reopening a recent session from the sidebar uses the mode you choose.
- **Native 3-tab Settings window** — Preferences are now grouped into General, Permissions, and Remote tabs with SF Symbol icons, matching macOS System Settings typography and footer layout.
- **One-click extension restart** — When a Claude Code extension update is downloaded, the update banner now offers a Restart Now button so you can pick up the new version without leaving Canopy.

### Changes

- **Removed the legacy multi-window shell** — Each session no longer opens its own AppKit window. The single-window model replaces it end-to-end, including reworked menu commands: ⌘N selects the Launcher, ⌘W is now context-aware (closes the active session, otherwise the focused window), ⌘0 brings the main window forward, ⌘1–9 jumps to the Nth visible sidebar row.
- **Main window frame is now persistent** — Window size and position are saved across launches and survive Stop Sessions and Close.

### Bug Fixes

- **SSH wrapper no longer leaks across sessions** — The SSH process wrapper path is now passed via an environment variable instead of being written to the shared settings file, fixing a bug where concurrent local and remote sessions could clobber each other's wrapper config and break /resume.
]]></description>
